methods.evalScript:
Evaluate the provided statements.

 If you've got a multi-line script; you must use this version.

:param s: (java.lang.String) - the string to evaluate
methods.evalStatement:
Evaluate the provided statement.

 Not suitable for use with scripts; because multiple statements will be ignored.

:param s: (java.lang.String) - the string to evaluate
methods.getPythonVersion:
Gets the Python interpreter version string.

:return: (java.lang.String) The Python interpreter version string.
methods.runScript:
Runs a Python script.

:param scriptFile: (java.lang.String) - the file to execute
methods.set:
Sets the variable within our session.

:param name: (java.lang.String) - the name of the variable to set.
:param value: (java.lang.Object) - the value of the variable.
